annotationA: Retinoblastoma protein homolog RBF2; Transcription regulatory region DNA binding; DNA binding; transcription factor binding; RNA polymerase II core promoter proximal region sequence-specific DNA binding transcription factor activity involved in negative regulation of transcription. It is involved in the biological process described with: regulation of cell cycle; negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; negative regulation of G1/S transition of mitotic cell cycle
annotationB: Serine/threonine-protein phosphatase PP2A 65 kDa regulatory subunit; The PR65 subunit of protein phosphatase 2A serves as a scaffolding molecule to coordinate the assembly of the catalytic subunit and a variable regulatory B subunit
